      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 608: The inline recorder has no duration or file-size limit, so a user can leave the dialog open indefinitely while the app keeps the microphone active and writes to storage. That is a privacy/resource risk and can fill app storage. Add bounded recording before prepare(), using limits consistent with message UX, for example:\n```suggestion\nsetMaxDuration(MAX_AUDIO_MESSAGE_DURATION_MS)\nsetMaxFileSize(MAX_AUDIO_MESSAGE_SIZE_BYTES)\nsetOnInfoListener { _, what, _ -\u003e\n    if (what \u003d\u003d MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_DURATION_REACHED ||\n        what \u003d\u003d MediaRecorder.MEDIA_RECORDER_INFO_MAX_FILESIZE_REACHED) {\n        stopAndSendAudioRecording()\n    }\n}\n```",
