      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 645: stopAndSendAudioRecording() returns early when either audioRecorder or audioRecordFile is null, but it does not release/delete whichever resource still exists. This can leak the recorder or leave a stale temp file if state becomes partially inconsistent during lifecycle/dialog callbacks. Snapshot both values, clear state, and always release/delete the available resource on invalid state.\n```suggestion\nval recorder \u003d audioRecorder\nval file \u003d audioRecordFile\naudioRecorder \u003d null\naudioRecordFile \u003d null\nif (recorder \u003d\u003d null || file \u003d\u003d null) {\n    recorder?.release()\n    file?.delete()\n    Toast.makeText(activity, R.string.audio_recorder_error, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n    return\n}\n```",
